The paper presents a method for online trajectory planning of mobile robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed algorithm involves optimization techniques to generate a time-dependent trajectory, which can be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY). The use of sampling-based techniques and model-based optimization also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the application of the proposed method to fluid autonomous navigation, which can be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG).
